# Project Structure & Organization

## App Router Structure
- **Locale-based routing:** All pages under `src/app/[locale]/` for i18n support
- **Route Groups:** Use `(auth)` for authentication pages, `(dashboard)` for protected routes
- **Layout Hierarchy:** Root layout in [layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/[locale]/layout.tsx), dashboard layout in [dashboard/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/[locale]/dashboard/layout.tsx)

## Component Organization
- **UI Components:** Reusable components in `src/components/ui/` (shadcn/ui)
- **Feature Components:** Business logic components in `src/components/`
- **Form Components:** Auth forms like [login-form.tsx](mdc:src/components/login-form.tsx) in components root
- **Layout Components:** Navigation and layout components in components root

## Services & Hooks
- **API Services:** Organized by feature in `src/services/` (auth, user, common)
- **Custom Hooks:** Service-specific hooks in respective service directories
- **State Management:** Zustand stores in `src/stores/`

## Internationalization
- **Routing:** Use `@/i18n/navigation` for locale-aware navigation
- **Translations:** Use `useTranslations` hook for all user-facing text
- **Language Support:** English and Korean as defined in [language-switcher.tsx](mdc:src/components/language-switcher.tsx)

## File Naming Conventions
- **kebab-case:** For file and directory names
- **PascalCase:** For component names and types
- **camelCase:** For functions and variables
- **Descriptive Names:** Use clear, descriptive names that indicate purpose
